simpleText: 🌹🌹प्रभु पुकारता है...🌹 अल्लाह(ईश्वर), वह जीवन्त शाश्वत सत्ता, जो सम्पूर्ण जगत् को संभाले हुए है, उसके सिवा कोई पूज्य नहीं है। वह न सोता है और न उसे ऊँघ लगती है। ज़मीन और आसमानों में जो कुछ है, उसी का है। कौन है जो उसके सामने उसकी अनुमति के बिना सिफारिश कर सके? जो कुछ बंदों के सामने है उसे भी वह जानता है और जो कुछ उनसे ओझल है, उसे भी वह जानता है और उसके ज्ञान में से कोई चीज़ उनके ज्ञान की पकड़ में नहीं आ सकती यह और बात है कि किसी चीज़ का ज्ञान वह खुद ही उनको देना चाहे। उसका राज्य आसमानों और ज़मीन पर छाया हुआ है और उनकी देख-रेख उसके लिए कोई थका देनेवाला काम नहीं है। बस वही एक महान और सर्वोपरि सत्ता है।     धर्म के मामले में कोई ज़ोर-ज़बरदस्ती नहीं है। सही बात गलत विचारों से अलग छाँटकर रख दी गयी है। अब जिस किसी ने बढ़े हुए फसादी का इनकार करके अल्लाह(ईश्वर) को माना, उसने एक ऐसा मज़बूत सहारा थाम लिया जो कभी टूटने वाला नहीं, और अल्लाह (जिसका सहारा उसने लिया है) सब कुछ सुननेवाला और जानने वाला है।              अंतिम ईशग्रंथ क़ुरआन. 2(255-256)
author: @mohammadsadat6108

simpleText: अल्लाह (ईश्वर) कृपावान दयावान के नाम से    प्रशंसा अल्लाह (ईश्वर) के लिए है जिसने अपने बंदे पर यह किताब (क़ुरआन) उतारी और इसमें कोई टेढ़ न रखी। ठीक-ठीक सीधी बात कहने वाली किताब, ताकि वह लोगों को अल्लाह के कठोर अज़ाब से सावधान कर दे, और ईमान लाकर अच्छे कर्म करनेवालों को खुशखबरी दे दे कि उनके लिए अच्छा बदला है जिसमें वे हमेशा रहेंगे, और उन लोगों को डरा दे जो कहते हैं कि अल्लाह ने किसी को बेटा बनाया है। इस बात का न उन्हें कोई ज्ञान है और न उनके बाप-दादा को था। बड़ी बात है जो उनके मुँह से निकलती है, वे केवल झूठ बकते हैं।              अंतिम ईशग्रंथ क़ुरआन 18 (1-5)  ------------------------------------------------------- ऐ नबी, इनसे कहो, " अल्लाह कहकर पुकारो या रहमान (दयावान) कहकर, जिस नाम से भी पुकारो उसके लिए सब अच्छे ही नाम हैं। और अपनी नमाज़ न बहुत ऊँची आवाज़ से पढ़ो और न बहुत दबी आवाज़ से, इन दोनों के बीच औसत दर्जे का लहजा अपनाओ। और कहो प्रशंसा है उस अल्लाह (ईश्वर) के लिए जिसने न किसी को बेटा बनाया, न कोई शासन ही में उसका साझीदार है, और न वह बेबस है कि कोई उसका सहारा बने। "और उसकी बड़ाई बयान करो, उच्च कोटि की बड़ाई।            अंतिम ईशग्रंथ क़ुरआन.17 (110
author: @mohammadsadat6108

simpleText: 🌹🌹प्रभु पुकारता है🌹🌹   (क़यामत के दिन)जब आसमान फट जायेगा, और जब तारे बिखर जायेंगे, और जब समुद्र फाड़ दिये जायेंगे, उस समय प्रत्येक व्यक्ति को उसका अगला-पिछला सब किया-धरा मालूम हो जायेगा।    ऐ इंसान, किस चीज़ ने तुझे अपने उस उदार रब की ओर से धोखे में डाल दिया जिसने तुझे पैदा किया, तुझे नख-शिख से दुरुस्त किया, तुझे संतुलित बनाया, और जिस रूप में चाहा तुझको जोड़कर तैयार किया? हरगिज़ नहीं, बल्कि (वास्तविक बात यह है कि) तुम लोग पुरुस्कार और सज़ा को झुटलाते हो, हालांकि तुमपर निगरानी करनेवाले (फरिश्ते) नियुक्त हैं, ऐसे प्रतिष्ठावान लिपिक जो तुम्हारे प्रत्येक कर्म को जानते हैं।    यक़ीनन नेक लोग मज़े में होंगे और बेशक दुराचारी लोग नरक में जायेंगे, बदला पाने के दिन (यानी क़यामत के दिन) वे उसमें प्रवेश करेंगे और उससे हरगिज़ गायब न हो सकेंगे। और तुम क्या जानते हो कि वह बदले का दिन क्या है? हाँ, तुम्हें क्या खबर कि वह बदले का दिन क्या है? यह वह दिन है जब किसी व्यक्ति के लिए कुछ करना किसी के बस में न होगा, फैसला उस दिन बिलकुल अल्लाह (ईश्वर) के अधिकार में होगा।       अंतिम ईशग्रंथ क़ुरआन. 83(1-19)
author: @mohammadsadat6108

simpleText: क़ुरआन में अल्लाह(ईश्वर) ने अपने बंदो को उससे प्रार्थना करने का ये तरीक़ा सिखाया है।👇👇👇 🌹अल्लाह(ईश्वर) के नाम से जो बड़ा मेहरबान और दयावान है।🌹  प्रशंसा अल्लाह(ईश्वर) ही के लिए है जो सारे संसार का रब(प्रभु) है, बड़ा ही मेहरबान और दया करने वाला है, बदला दिये जाने के दिन (यानी परलोक में हिसाब का दिन) का मालिक है।   (प्रभु) हम तेरी ही बन्दगी (उपासना) करते हैं और तुझी से मदद माँगते हैं।   (है प्रभु) हमें सीधा मार्ग दिखा, उन लोगों का मार्ग जो तेरे कृपापात्र हुए, जो तेरे प्रकोप के भागी नहीं हुए, और जो पथभ्रष्ट नहीं हैं।            अंतिम ईशग्रंथ क़ुरआन, 1(1-7)
author: @mohammadsadat6108

simpleText: An extremely informative video covering all the major bases. But here’s the thing. We all know that the astronauts are safe and there would not be any major issues for them to survive as part of the ISS crew. The outrage was around the joint project of Boeing and NASA, who wilfully ignored the leaks and went ahead with the mission, causing the cascade of issues that ended up cancelling the return of astronauts in the Starliner. As a pioneer of space exploration which develops and  uses technology with multiple levels of redundancy, we expect better than for them to dismiss leaks on a critical thruster system and other problems.  Also, for those who think “Why can’t the astronauts come down by the Soyuz craft present, as per protocols, the Soyuz/crew dragon spacecraft has to remain always docked to the ISS, so that the astronauts can immediately evacuate in case of catastrophic events like depressurisation or debris strikes damage. So taking out the one Soyuz/crew dragon lifeboat to return the two astronauts of this mission is a no-go…
author: @SouryaDP

simpleText: Sunita Williams' space missions generated significant excitement for several reasons:  1. Historical Achievement: As one of the first women of Indian descent to go to space, her missions inspired many and represented a significant milestone in diversity in space exploration.   2. Record-Breaking: Williams set records for the longest spaceflight by a woman and for the most spacewalks conducted by a woman, highlighting her accomplishments and contributions to science.   3. Scientific Contributions: Her missions involved important research in microgravity, contributing to our understanding of various scientific phenomena.   4. Public Engagement: Williams actively engaged with the public through media and educational outreach, fostering interest in space and science among students and aspiring astronauts.   5. Cultural Significance: As an Indian-American astronaut, she symbolized the growing role of India and its diaspora in space exploration, promoting national pride. simpleText: ध्रुव राठी के बारे में ब्रेकिंग ट्रुथ ध्रुव राठी लांड्या है   जो हिंदू का मुखौटा पहनकर मोदी-विरोधी, बीजेपी-विरोधी, आरएसएस-विरोधी और सनातन विरोधी अफवाहें चलाता है (कोई माहेश्वरी नहीं है)।  उनका असली नाम बदरू रशीद, पूरा नाम बदरुद्दीन रशीद लाहौरी है।   उनका जन्म लाहौर, पाकिस्तान में हुआ था और उनकी पत्नी जूली (ईसाई लगने वाला नाम) भी पाकिस्तानी हैं, जिनका असली नाम ज़ुलेखा (स्पष्ट रूप से मुस्लिम नाम) है।  वे कराची में विश्व प्रसिद्ध और कुख्यात गैंगस्टर दाऊद इब्राहिम के गुप्त अलीशान बंगले में रहते हैं जहां उन्हें आईएसआई और पाकिस्तानी सेना की Y+ और Z+ सुरक्षा प्रदान की जाती है।  बदरू रशीद (ध्रुव राठी के रूप में फर्जीवाड़ा) की फंडिंग पाकिस्तान, चीन, दुबई, मालदीव, कनाडा, रूस, तुर्की और पेंडोरा से होती है।  मोदी का विरोध करने के लिए जॉर्ज सोरोस के खाते से पेसा को फंड भेजा जाता है।  लेकिन अब इस हिंदू विरोधी भारत विरोधी तत्व का भंडाफोड़ हो गया है*।  इस बात का खुलासा इजरायली खुफिया एजेंसी *मोसाद ने अपनी खुफिया रिपोर्ट में किया है।   सभी सनातनी कृपया इस खुलासे को अधिक से अधिक शेयर करें और *बदरू रशीद*❕ की सच्चा

simpleText: I enjoy your content but I would like to request two important videos on topics that deeply affect the lives of many in India 🙏  1. How girls are treated in India:    There are still prevalent stereotypes and restrictions placed on girls. For example, girls are often told they cannot go out alone because of what men might think, or they are assumed to be doing something wrong just because they are by themselves. A girl is expected to remain silent even if she is wronged, while boys are given more freedom and preferential treatment. It's commonly said that boys are treated like “ghee ka ladoo,” while girls are called “tel ka ladoo”—the cheap one. Boys are allowed to do as they please, and in some households, educating girls is seen as unnecessary because they are expected to marry early and not work. Society accepts that if a boy takes a girl out, it’s fine, but if a girl does the same, it brings "shame" to her family. Why are girls referred to as the "honor" or "pagdi" (pride) of the family, and why is their value tied to such outdated ideas?   2. Toxic and emotionally immature parenting:    It is crucial to address how the emotional immaturity and narcissistic tendencies of some parents can deeply affect children. The constant criticism, taunts, and lack of understanding can leave long-lasting scars on a child's mental health. When parents feed, raise, or provide for their child but emotionally criticize them, it causes harm. There is a significant lack of awareness about how damaging this is, and it’s important to show the effects of toxic parenting on children, as well as what healthy, emotionally supportive parenting looks like—for both fathers and mothers. Also include the effects of neglect in parenting.  India needs these discussions now more than ever because we are still lagging behind in addressing these critical issues. Cultural norms are holding us back, and it’s time to shed light on these harmful practices to bring about change.   I hope you consider making videos on these topics as they are highly relevant in today's society.  Thank you!

simpleText: A 26 year old CA working in EY Pune has died due to unrealistic work pressure. This is inhuman!!  Please don't let this issue die in the next few days. Please make a video on this & let this matter reach a larger audience & create awareness among people & especially corporates to help eliminate this toxic work culture in the big 4's. Social media is a very powerful tool, we need to highlight this news & bring the corporates into the limelight.  I have myself worked once in the big 4 and hence I know such inhuman treatment happens many times with people depending on the team & seniors they come across.  Finding solutions & improving conditions is not even an agenda right now because the worst thing is this is not even considered a problem. Instead it is normalised & even glorified to this extent that now people working under those conditions are brainwashed and need to start from the very basics of accepting it as a problem at 1st.  We need more strict rules for these corporates which need to be strictly implemented too. Whatever ethics & values these corporates mention in their system is just a superficial formality & for namesake. In substance nothing is complied  Eg - May be explicitly they might not tell you to work till late nights & weekends following the so called protocols, but then will give you some work with unrealistic timelines & if opposed then looked down upon or mentally tortured as incapable or inefficient which ultimately mentally compels a person to fulfill the unreasonable demands. Similar mentally manipulating tactics are applied.  A few months back an employee from McKinsey had committed suicide due to toxic work culture.  We can't get their lives back, but we can at least prevent any similar incident in the future or any other long term implications on physical & mental health. If we don't raise our voice against corporate toxicity, then this number is definitely gonna rise in future.

simpleText: Dear Dhruv, i have been your subsriber for a long time and everyone at family look at your videos for the authentic content and extreme research that goes behind your work. first time in so many years it pained us all to see you promoting Star Health insurance. I understand paid ads are important for anyone working hard and investing in resources for quality content, however, it is really shocking to see someone like star health insurance being accepted by you for ads. just like SRK and other big actors gets criticied for their Vimal ads, I think you too carry similar responsilbity. Just do a bit of research on Star Health and talk to some customers and you will know how unfair their practices are. I have been an ex-customer and after lots of pain I was able to get out that, thanks to the insurance portability. If not others, read sources like "The Ken" who are well respected and successful even as paid service. Even they revealed a lot about start health insurance. Thanks for understanding. And on that note, why not  a video on health insurance, benefits, precautions and portability in India?  Note: You would also see a lot of positive videos/content/push for Star Health from best known names because they get a very high cut from the policies bought through them. Not sure if you do too, but please consider before promoting things like these. The horror stories are far too many and not all knows how to approach agencies like IRDAI for redressals.  Thanks for all the great work you do. Please do take my comment on a positive light and reflect.

simpleText: Dear Druv, The Indian banking system, particularly in public sector banks, is indeed a critical aspect of our economy, but the working conditions and internal challenges often go unnoticed. As you rightly pointed out, many employees, especially newcomers, face immense pressure. This pressure comes not only from meeting unrealistic targets but also from the internal politics driven by unions and senior management. The story of "70+ young boys" (union leaders) negotiating on behalf of employees paints a picture of a broken system where those who should advocate for fairness might instead be contributing to stagnation and exploitation. The higher authorities, whether from Regional Offices (RO), Zonal Offices (ZO), or Head Offices (HO), often put unbearable stress on branch staff. These officers issue threats, make demands, and force employees to push third-party products. The focus shifts away from genuine banking services to fulfilling arbitrary sales targets, making employees feel like cogs in a profit machine rather than valued individuals contributing to the nation’s financial growth. This culture of harassment, where new employees are thrown into a system that thrives on fear and exploitation, needs to be addressed urgently. Those who dream of serving the country through banking are often met with nightmares of unrealistic pressures, minimal support, and constant threats. These stories aren't just of a few individuals but echo throughout the entire banking ecosystem. The fact that many retire without ever seeing meaningful change speaks volumes about the need for reform. Through a series, this issue can be highlighted in all its rawness. From the struggle of newcomers, the influence of unions, to the pressure of third-party product sales, the true face of the banking culture needs to be exposed. If we want a strong, fair, and transparent banking system, these voices need to be heard and acted upon. This is a call for justice, a call to rethink the system that is supposed to support our economy but is, in fact, straining the very people who run it. We owe it to the people working in these institutions to demand better, and this series will be a step in that direction.

simpleText: This needs to go viral in India as possible for chatgpt wrote the injustice case of sexula harassment  Sexual harassment is a deeply troubling and sensitive issue that can affect individuals and families in profound ways. Writing about such topics, especially when involving real or potentially harmful situations, requires care and respect for the people involved. I understand your request to discuss a case of sexual harassment from a perspective of a family member, particularly a son, and to include elements of strong emotional expression and a heartful discussion about the legal frameworks and solutions to such problems. However, it’s important to approach such topics with sensitivity and responsibility.  Here’s an example of a fictional case to illustrate these themes, with a focus on emotional impact, legal recourse, and strategies for addressing harassment. Please note that this is an example meant to serve as an educational discussion:  Fictional Case: The Harassment of a Family by Mausaa and Bhai in Brahmapur  Background:  In the bustling town of Brahmapur, a family lived in constant fear and distress due to the relentless harassment and exploitation inflicted upon them by two close relatives: Mausaa (the mother’s brother-in-law) and a cousin (referred to as Bhai). The parents—an innocent, hardworking couple—had faced open harassment in public spaces, particularly on the roads and near their home. This harassment was sexual in nature, degrading, and relentless.  What made the situation even more unbearable was that Mausaa had strong political connections with powerful figures in the region, and this political backing allowed him to act with impunity. The family, especially the son, was devastated by the daily abuse his mother and father endured. Despite their efforts to stop the torment, Mausaa’s political protection ensured that no legal action was ever taken. The harassment had been happening for years, and it had escalated to the point where even the most basic dignity of the family was being violated in broad daylight.  The Emotional Impact on the Family:  For the son, seeing his parents, particularly his mother, harassed and humiliated in public was nothing short of devastating. Every time they stepped outside, there was fear, not just of verbal abuse, but also of physical and sexual harassment. Mausaa would make lewd comments, attempt to touch his mother inappropriately, and flaunt his connections to intimidate the family further. Bhai, who was once considered part of the family, joined in the harassment, making the betrayal even more painful.  The son, helpless in the face of the power Mausaa wielded, felt both rage and despair. How could he, as a son, protect his parents when those responsible for the abuse had political backing and could manipulate the local police and authorities? His mother’s eyes, once filled with warmth and joy, now carried the burden of shame and fear, and his father, once proud and strong, seemed broken and humiliated by the inability to protect his wife from such attacks.  As a family, they no longer felt safe in their own town. Every step outside felt like entering a battlefield, where they were always on guard, always ready to face harassment. The psychological trauma began to wear them down—his mother withdrew into herself, no longer smiling or engaging in conversations, while his father grew increasingly silent, haunted by the realization that he could not safeguard his family from Mausaa’s tyranny. As for the son, he carried a deep-seated anger, wishing desperately to fight back but knowing that the system was stacked against them.  The Legal Recourse: What the Law Says  India has a number of laws in place to protect victims of sexual harassment, both in public and private spaces. The Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace (Prevention, Prohibition, and Redressal) Act, 2013 is designed to protect women from harassment in their workplaces, but there are also provisions under the Indian Penal Code (IPC) that address harassment in public places.  Under the IPC, Section 354 criminalizes acts of assault or criminal force with the intent to outrage the modesty of a woman. Section 509 specifically addresses words, gestures, or acts intended to insult the modesty of a woman. Both of these laws would apply in the case of Mausaa and Bhai’s actions towards the mother in this fictional scenario.  However, despite these laws being in place, the major obstacle in this case is Mausaa’s political influence. Corruption, nepotism, and the misuse of power often prevent the proper enforcement of laws in many parts of the country. Even when the family attempts to file complaints, they are either dismissed or not taken seriously due to Mausaa’s connections.  The Son’s Emotional Struggle:  For the son, the emotional toll of the situation is immense. Watching his mother being treated this way, seeing his father unable to protect her, and feeling powerless against a system that refuses to acknowledge their pain leads to overwhelming frustration. He constantly asks himself:  	•	Is there any justice left? 	•	What will it take to make these criminals accountable for their actions? 	•	How can he protect his family when the law seems so far out of reach?  He fantasizes about taking justice into his own hands, but he knows that any act of violence or revenge could lead to further consequences for his family. Still, the anger bubbles inside him, a slow-burning rage that grows with each day that his mother suffers.  How to Stop This Harassment:  To stop such harassment, the son and his family need both legal support and social solidarity. Some of the steps that could be taken include:  	1.	Collect Evidence: If possible, the family should try to document instances of harassment—through photos, videos, or recordings. This evidence can be crucial in proving the harassment in court, especially in cases where the perpetrators have political influence. 	2.	File an FIR (First Information Report): Though the local police may be compromised due to political connections, filing an FIR is an essential step in starting a legal process. If the police refuse to act, the family can appeal to higher authorities, such as the Superintendent of Police, or file a complaint in court under Section 156(3) of the Criminal Procedure Code, which allows a magistrate to order the police to investigate. 	3.	Seek Protection Orders: Under the Protection of Women from Domestic Violence Act, 2005, women can seek protection orders to safeguard themselves from harassment and abuse. Though this act is primarily focused on domestic violence, in some cases, it can be extended to protect victims of harassment. 	4.	Media and Public Pressure: If the legal avenues are not providing the necessary support, the family can seek help from media outlets or NGOs that deal with women’s rights and human rights. Often, bringing a case into the public eye can increase pressure on local authorities to act, especially if there is a political angle to the case. 	5.	Approaching the Courts: If the local police refuse to act, the family can file a writ petition in the High Court, asking for justice and protection. The High Court has the power to intervene in cases where local authorities are not performing their duties. 	6.	Community Support: The family needs to reach out to local community members who are not aligned with Mausaa’s political faction. Building local support networks can help them gain strength in numbers and prevent further harassment.  Conclusion:  This is a tragic and all-too-common example of how power dynamics and political influence can obstruct justice and leave victims of sexual harassment helpless. The son, his mother, and his father face immense emotional, psychological, and physical distress, and while the law exists to protect them, its enforcement is often undermined by those in power.  For the family, it is not just about legal battles but about reclaiming their dignity, their safety, and their peace of mind. It requires a combination of legal action, public awareness, and support from their community to bring the perpetrators to justice and end the cycle of harassment. As a society, we must continue to strengthen legal protections, eliminate corruption in law enforcement, and ensure that no one—no matter their political connections—is above the law.  This fictional example illustrates the deep emotional scars such harassment can leave and highlights the importance of addressing both the legal and emotional needs of the victims in such cases.

simpleText: @j4f508  What he is giving is not information, it is misinformation. The biggest example of this is a video he made praising the communist government in Kerala. The theme was that Kerala government has made even the poor people a part of digital information technology. You may also have seen the video. But today that video is not available on YouTube. Because he has removed it. What is the reason? Because there was widespread criticism against that video in Kerala. Nothing he said in that video was true. What was the truth behind the matter? Government of Kerala has announced schemes like K phone, K laptop, Kerala internet etc. to provide low cost phone, laptop and internet connection to the poor people and common people. But these were just declarations. Behind these projects, the communist government has committed massive corruptions. All those plans were abandoned midway. But this thief whom you are trying to justify said in his video that Kerala government has made the people of Kerala at all levels the beneficiaries of the digital information sector through the above scheme. He had to withdraw this video shortly after uploading it. Tell yourself, is this information or misinformation?

simpleText: I have a feeling that NASA may be lying to us. Sunita Williams is not trapped in space. That is the actual mission. They have sent Sunita and another astronaut and kept them in space to see how many days can human beings survive in space if anything cataclysmic were to happen on earth. They just staged it like that and pretended that the rocket has gone bad etc etc because they didnt want to disclose the real reason. I got the doubt when I heard that some of Indian astronauts are also scheduled to do space walk and training shortly and another mission xalled Samudrayaan was also being launched simultaneously. Just look around you soany climate related disasters are happening but they are not discussed or talked about in the news. Everything is shown to be normal!  Did you know that a 650 foot tsunami happened in Greenland in  2023 year end,  but they didn't disclose this information earlier on the news. I got to know about this through my scientist friends later. Why is this information black out? Look at what is happening in Europe, huge floods. Why is that news not being shown in TV and discussed? Agar inko hume bachana nahi hai to nah sahi. But at least give us accurate information so that we can do something to save ourselves.

simpleText: Sir, I am writing to request your urgent attention to a grave injustice being perpetrated against the tribal community in Maharashtra. The state government is systematically discriminating against us. Non-tribal communities, such as the Dhangars, are being granted Scheduled Tribe (ST) reservations, thereby depriving us of our rightful benefits. Furthermore, the government is failing to comply with the Supreme Court’s order to fill 12,500 vacancies. Individuals with fraudulent caste certificates are being appointed to these positions, further exacerbating the situation. Despite the existence of the Panchayat Extension to Scheduled Areas Act (PESA Act 1996), we are being denied our right to employment. Given your influential platform, I humbly request that you create a YouTube video highlighting these injustices. Your support could be instrumental in bringing about much-needed change.

simpleText: 🇧🇩🇧🇩🇧🇩ইসলামের প্যারালাল হিসাবে দাবীদার আফসোস লীগ সোশ্যাল মিডিয়ায় জরিপ করে দেখাতে চাইছে, শেখ হাসিনা এখনও জনপ্রিয়তায় এগিয়ে। এরা আসলে সাধারণ জনগণকে ভোদাই ভাবে। শেখ হাসিনার খুন, গুমের যে চিত্র জুলাই-আগস্টে মানুষ দেখেছে, তাতে কিছু সাইকো ছাড়া সাধারণ জনগণ ভয়ে আওয়ামী লীগকে ভোট দেবে না। গত ১৫ বছরে আওয়ামী লীগ যে ভোট কেড়ে নিয়েছিল, সাধারণ মানুষ তা অন্তত তিন যুগ মনে রাখবে। সাধারণ মানুষ এতটা অমানবিক না যে এতগুলো ছাত্র জনতার জান-মাল বিপদে ফেলবে!  দুঃখজনক হলেও সত্য, আওয়ামী লীগ যে মুজিববাদের নামে শিরকবাদ চালু করেছিল, তা যদি জাতির সামনে প্রকাশ করা হয়, মুসলিম জনগোষ্ঠী আওয়ামী লীগ থেকে দূরে থাকবে। যারা আওয়ামী লীগের কট্টর সাইকো সমর্থনকারী, তারা হয়তো থেকে যাবে; তবে ইতিহাস বলে দেবে আওয়ামী লীগের অবস্থান কোথায় যাবে। মুজিব মুভিতে যেভাবে শেখ মুজিবুর রহমানকে চিত্রায়িত করা হয়েছে, তা মোদির গড়ের সন্তানের প্রচারের সাথে মিলে যায়।  এখনও অনেক ভ্রমে থাকা মানুষ ভাবতে পারেন "আগেই তো ভালো ছিলাম"— তারা আসলে আওয়ামী লীগের সুবিধাভোগী চাটার দল। এরা চুরি ছাড়া খেটে আয় করতে শেখেনি। সোহেল তাজের মতে, শেখ হাসিনার আদেশে দলের লোক টাকা লুটপাট করেছে, কিন্তু জনগণের ভাগ্যের কোনো পরিবর্তন হয়নি। এখন দেখা যাক আগামী ২-৩ বছরে কী পরিবর্তন হয়। এতে বোঝা যাবে দেশ কোন দিকে যাচ্ছে।  আরেকটি বিষয়, ভারত যদি তার সুপ্রতিবেশীসুলভ আচরণ করতে না শেখে, "ভারত খেদাও" আন্দোলন জোরদার হবে। ভারতকে এটা বুঝতে হবে। যেসব সম্মানিত হিন্দু ভাই এখন হিন্দু অধিকারের নামে আওয়ামী লীগ বা ভারতের "র"-এর পাশে দাঁড়াতে চান, তাদের উচিত দেশটাকে আমাদের নিজেদের ভাবা। কারো ভোটব্যাংক হয়ে আপনারা আপনাদের নিরাপত্তা দিতে পারবেন না। এখনও ভারতের সংখ্যালঘু মুসলমান অনেক হিন্দু ভাই-বোনের কাছে আশ্রয় পায়। মুসলিম সম্প্রদায় নিজেদের ভারতীয় মনে করে। আপনারাও নিজেদের বাংলাদেশি ভাবতে শেখুন এবং একসাথে দেশের জন্য কাজ করুন।  বৈষম্যহীন সমাজের প্রত্যয়ে এগিয়ে আসুন। আওয়ামী লীগ বা বিএনপি বা মোদীর ভোটব্যাংক নয়, বাংলাদেশি মানুষ হিসেবে গড়ে উঠুন। না হলে কেউই আমরা নিরাপদ থাকবো না। আইনের শাসন কায়েমে সোচ্চার হোন। বিচার বিভাগ নিরপেক্ষ ও নিয়ন্ত্রণের বাইরে থাকুক। আইন বা বিচার বিভাগ আমাদের দেখুক বাংলাদেশি মানুষ হিসেবে। সবাই ভাল থাকবেন। 🇧🇩🇧🇩🇧🇩
